book:
    The MATE Usability Project

2002-2010
Calum Benson, Adam Elman, Seth Nickell, colin z robertson

2010-03-02
2.2.1



This document tells you how to create applications that look right, behave
properly, and fit into the MATE user interface as a whole. It is written for
interface designers, graphic artists and software developers who will be creating
software for the MATE environment. Both specific advice on making effective use
of interface elements, and the philosophy and general design principles behind
the MATE interface are covered.





